<a name="Test Toggles">
<h3>
2.6.3  Test Toggles
</h3>
</a>
<p>This section covers how to toggle a pre-generated test.
<p>This feature is only available for teachers only.
	For more information on <br>teacher's functions,
	<a href="teach-func.html"> click here.</a>

<p>Teachers have the authorization to turn on/off of a specific test to monitor<br>the flow of the class and to futher prevent students from taking the wrong test.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Initial screen">
<a name="Initial screen">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle1_1.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 1.1:  Initial screen.  </p>

</a>
<br>
<a name="Figure Initial screen">
<a name="Initial screen">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle1_2.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 1.2:  Access Drop Down Menu.  </p>
<hr>
<br>
<p>The intial screen contains a list of user's(teacher) current classes they are teaching. Figure 1.1
<p>User clicks on the <tt>drop down menu</tt> to access the <tt>toggles</tt> of all tests within a desired class. Figure 1.2
<p>
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Click on dropdown ">
<a name="Expanded menus tab">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle2_1.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 2.1:  Turn Toggles On  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>After the user clicks on the <tt>drop down menu</tt>, a list of tests that is assigned to the class will display. Figure 2.1
<p>The user selects a desired test to be turned on and the on/off toggle button is directly to the right of the desired test.
<p>
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Click on dropdown ">
<a name="Expanded menus tab">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle2_2.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 2.2:  Toggle Button  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>Tests are preset as toggled off. User must click on the toggle button (the toggle will display as green) to turn on the test.
<p>
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Click on dropdown ">
<a name="Expanded menus tab">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle3.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 3:  Save Changes  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>
<p>The user updates the toggle changes by clicking on the <tt>save</tt> button.
<p>The test is now live for students to attempt and make progress upon.
<p>After all the students took the test, teacher have the option to view statistics of class results as well as individual<br> student's score in
	<a href="statistics.html">Statistics.</a>

<p>
